\f0  Compute compatibility score (class code + endpoint analysis) 
\f10 \'a9\'c0\'a9\'a4\'a9\'a4
\f0  Maintain local device inventory (HashMap<DeviceId, DeviceInfo>) \uc0\u9492 \u9472 \u9472  Emit hotplug events to orchestrator via WebSocket\cb1 \
\cb4 USB/IP Control Subsystem: 
\f10 \'a9\'c0\'a9\'a4\'a9\'a4
\f0  Linux: subprocess wrapper around usbip CLI \uc0\u9474  
\f10 \'a9\'c0\'a9\'a4\'a9\'a4
\f0  usbip bind --busid=\'a0(server role) \uc0\u9474  
\f10 \'a9\'c0\'a9\'a4\'a9\'a4
\f0  usbip unbind --busid=\'a0(server role) \uc0\u9474  
\f10 \'a9\'c0\'a9\'a4\'a9\'a4
\f0  usbip attach -r\'a0-b\'a0(client role) \uc0\u9474  \uc0\u9492 \u9472 \u9472  usbip detach -p\'a0(client role) 
\f10 \'a9\'c0\'a9\'a4\'a9\'a4
\f0  Windows: subprocess wrapper around usbipd.exe \uc0\u9474  
\f10 \'a9\'c0\'a9\'a4\'a9\'a4
\f0  usbipd bind --busid=\'a0\uc0\u9474  
\f10 \'a9\'c0\'a9\'a4\'a9\'a4
\f0  usbipd unbind --busid=\'a0\uc0\u9474  \uc0\u9492 \u9472 \u9472  usbipd attach --remote=\'a0--busid=\'a0
\f10 \'a9\'c0\'a9\'a4\'a9\'a4
\f0  Parse CLI output for success/failure and error codes 
\f10 \'a9\'c0\'a9\'a4\'a9\'a4
\f0  Implement retry logic (3 attempts with exponential backoff) \uc0\u9492 \u9472 \u9472  Report operation outcome to orchestrator\cb1 \
\cb4 Orchestrator Communication Subsystem: 
\f10 \'a9\'c0\'a9\'a4\'a9\'a4
\f0  WebSocket client connection to orchestrator (wss://) 
\f10 \'a9\'c0\'a9\'a4\'a9\'a4
\f0  JWT authentication header on connection 
\f10 \'a9\'c0\'a9\'a4\'a9\'a4
\f0  Heartbeat: ping/pong every 30 seconds 
\f10 \'a9\'c0\'a9\'a4\'a9\'a4
\f0  Message queue: buffer commands when network is unavailable 
\f10 \'a9\'c0\'a9\'a4\'a9\'a4
\f0  Reconnect: exponential backoff (5s, 10s, 20s, 40s, max 120s) 
\f10 \'a9\'c0\'a9\'a4\'a9\'a4
\f0  On reconnect: send full state.snapshot message \uc0\u9492 \u9472 \u9472  Process incoming commands: cmd.bind, cmd.unbind, cmd.attach, cmd.detach\cb1 \
\cb4 mDNS Discovery Subsystem: 
\f10 \'a9\'c0\'a9\'a4\'a9\'a4
\f0  Announce: _unisonbridge-agent._tcp.local on startup 
\f10 \'a9\'c0\'a9\'a4\'a9\'a4
\f0  TXT record: version=1.0;os=linux;hostname=;port=8765 
\f10 \'a9\'c0\'a9\'a4\'a9\'a4
\f0  Browse: listen for other agents and orchestrator announcements \uc0\u9492 \u9472 \u9472  Unannounce: on graceful shutdown\cb1 \
\cb4 Virtual Device Subsystem (Linux only): 
\f10 \'a9\'c0\'a9\'a4\'a9\'a4
\f0  PipeWire virtual sink management (pw-loopback) 
\f10 \'a9\'c0\'a9\'a4\'a9\'a4
\f0  PulseAudio null sink management (pactl) 
\f10 \'a9\'c0\'a9\'a4\'a9\'a4
\f0  v4l2loopback management (modprobe, GStreamer pipelines) 
\f10 \'a9\'c0\'a9\'a4\'a9\'a4
\f0  USB Gadget ConfigFS management (HID, mass storage) \uc0\u9492 \u9472 \u9472  GStreamer pipeline management (launch, monitor, teardown)\cb1 \
\cb4 Log Collection Subsystem: 
\f10 \'a9\'c0\'a9\'a4\'a9\'a4
\f0  Linux: journalctl -k -g 'usbip|vhci' (kernel logs) 
\f10 \'a9\'c0\'a9\'a4\'a9\'a4
\f0  Linux: journalctl -u usbipd (daemon logs) 
\f10 \'a9\'c0\'a9\'a4\'a9\'a4
\f0  Windows: Windows Event Log (usbipd-win service events) 
\f10 \'a9\'c0\'a9\'a4\'a9\'a4
\f0  All platforms: agent operational log (structured JSON) \uc0\u9492 \u9472 \u9472  Stream to orchestrator via WebSocket log.entry events
