\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec3 Client agent has vhci-hcd capability \uc0\u9474  \u9660  Orchestrator sends cmd.bind to Machine A's agent: \{ "type": "cmd.bind", "device_id": "uuid", "bus_id": "1-1.5" \} \u9474  \u9660  Machine A agent executes: usbip bind --busid=1-1.5 \u8594  Reports success: \{ "type": "bind.success", "bus_id": "1-1.5" \} \u9474  \u9660  Orchestrator sends cmd.attach to Machine B's agent: \{ "type": "cmd.attach", "server_ip": "192.168.1.10", "bus_id": "1-1.5" \} \u9474  \u9660  Machine B agent executes: usbip attach -r 192.168.1.10 -b 1-1.5 \u8594  Reports success: \{ "type": "attach.success", "port": 0 \} \u9474  \u9660  (TCP connection established directly between agents on port 3240) \u9474  \u9660  Orchestrator updates ConnectionRegistry: state = ACTIVE \u9474  \u9660  Orchestrator broadcasts connection.state_changed to all UI clients \u9474  \u9660  Dashboard updates: device shows "In use by workstation02" \u9474  \u9660  Orchestrator writes audit log entry: user=alice, action=ATTACH, device=FT232, server=workstation01, client=workstation02, timestamp=..., outcome=success
\f4\fs30 \
