\cf3 ### Flow 3: Hotplug Device Removal During Active Connection\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa80\partightenfactor0

\f0\fs32 \cf3 User unplugs USB device from Machine A while it's shared to Machine B \uc0\u9474  \u9660  Linux udev emits REMOVE event \u9474  \u9660  Machine A agent receives hotplug notification (libudev callback) \u9474  \u9660  Agent checks: is this device currently bound to USB/IP stub? Yes \u8594  attempt graceful unbind (usbip unbind) \u9474  \u9660  Agent emits device.removed event to orchestrator: \{ "type": "device.removed", "device_id": "uuid", "reason": "physically_removed" \} \u9474  \u9660  Orchestrator updates DeviceRegistry: device.status = REMOVED Orchestrator updates ConnectionRegistry: connection.state = ERROR, connection.error = "device removed from server" \u9474  \u9660  Orchestrator sends cmd.detach to Machine B's agent (cleanup) \u9474  \u9660  Machine B agent executes: usbip detach -p 0 \u9474  \u9660  Orchestrator broadcasts: device.removed \u8594  UI shows device removed from Machine A connection.state_changed (ERROR) \u8594  UI shows connection error with message \u9474  \u9660  If auto-reconnect policy exists: orchestrator schedules reconnect check \u8594  When device reappears (next hotplug add event), re-execute connection flow
\f4\fs30 \
